<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to manually send an email template.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Manually sending an email template:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Ticket system</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Use the search function (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>) and open the ticket that should be edited.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Send email template</strong> (<span class="icon purple"><i class="fa fa-envelope-o  "></i></span>). <br>
→ The <strong>Send email template</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select an email template from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Send email template</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-cog  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If the ticket is not linked to a customer, the email template cannot be sent. If you manually send email templates, the signature displayed in these emails is the signature that was saved in the system’s email settings.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="2900">10. Automatically sending an email template</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Setup » CRM » Ticket system » Events</strong> menu, you use filters to select tickets and then assign the tickets to automatic procedures which are carried out by an event procedure. One example would be that when a ticket enters the system, the email template is automatically sent to the customer and all ticket owners receive a reminder via e-mail template when the ticket is in a certain status (in our example Status <strong>All</strong> and assigned to a certain owner (in our example Owner <strong>plentytest</strong>).</p>
</div>
<div id="image-event-procedure-automatic-reply" class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/crm/assets/crm-ticket-system-event-procedure-automatic-reply-to-customer.png" alt="Example of an event procedure “Automatic reply to customer”" width="640" height="360">
</div>
<div class="title">Figure 1. Example of an event procedure “Automatic reply to customer”</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>It is important that you insert the templates variables available in plentymarkets in the email template as described in <a href="/en/crm/using-the-ticket-system#2900">Manually sending an email template</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Set up an event procedure also for the despatch of messages and comments</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Note that an event procedure also has to be set up for sending messages and comments via email. If you answer your customers with messages in the ticket system, you need to set up an event procedure that sends the last ticket message as an email. Otherwise the customer does not receive your answer.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For further information about customer communication in the ticket system, refer to the chapters <a href="/en/crm/using-the-ticket-system#2400">Adding a message</a>, <a href="/en/crm/using-the-ticket-system#2500">Adding a comment</a>, <a href="/en/crm/using-the-ticket-system#2600">Assigning a topic</a>, <a href="/en/crm/using-the-ticket-system#2700">Entering answers to FAQs</a> and <a href="/en/crm/using-the-ticket-system#2800">Manually sending an email template</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For further information on how to set up event procedures, refer to the <a href="/en/automation/event procedures">Event procedures</a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
<h3 id="_setting_up_the_event_procedure_new_ticket_message" class="discrete">Setting up the event procedure “New ticket message”</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up an <a href="/en/automation/event-procedures">event procedure</a> to receive an email every time that a new ticket message is received in your ticket system, for example.</p>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title">Setting up an event procedure</div>
<div class="content">
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » CRM » Ticket system » Events</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add event procedure</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus-square  "></i></span>).<br>
→ The <strong>Create new event procedure</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>Event</strong> as listed in <a href="#table-event-procedure-new-message-ticket-system">Table 9</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as listed in <a href="#table-event-procedure-new-message-ticket-system">Table 9</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
