<h2 id="3500">16. Editing tickets</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A ticket is made up of several messages and comments. The comments can only be read internally. In addition, you can add files and tasks to a ticket. Tickets can also be added up to build a chain: One ticket can have several children and these children can have children themselves.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Which settings you may carry out in a ticket’s tabs is described in the following sub-chapters.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="3600">16.1. Displaying and editing ticket settings</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can see all the settings of your ticket at a glance in the <strong>CRM » Ticket system » Open ticket</strong> menu in the <strong>Ticket</strong> tab. You can also change some of the settings here. <a href="#table-edit-ticket">Table 13</a> explains the setting options for your tickets.</p>
