</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="3700">16.2. Displaying the contact data</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>Customer</strong> tab of a ticket in the <strong>CRM » Ticket system</strong> menu contains the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#300">contact data</a> as it is also found in the <strong>CRM » Contacts » [Open contact]</strong> menu. You can also edit the contact data record here. This tab is only visible if the ticket is linked to a contact.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="3800">16.3. Showing orders</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Ticket system</strong> and see the customer’s orders in the <strong>Search orders</strong> tab of the ticket. You can search for orders and edit them in this menu. This tab is only visible if the ticket is linked to a contact.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="3900">16.4. Showing the attachment</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Go to <strong>CRM » Ticket system</strong> and see all file attachments that were uploaded in the <strong>Attachment</strong> tab of the ticket. Both your customers and staff members can attach documents to tickets and have permanent access to them. The number of attachments is displayed in parentheses in the tab’s title. Once the first file has been successfully uploaded, a table is displayed. The table lists the file name, the name of the employee or customer who uploaded the file as well as the visibility and the date.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The image files immediately open after the click. If this is not supported by the browser, the file can be downloaded. With the setting <strong>Visibility</strong>, you decide whether the file is also visible for your customers or only for you and your employees.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you activated the option <strong>Attachment</strong> using the <a href="/en/welcome/customise-system#160">Customise layout</a> function in the <strong>CRM » Ticket system</strong> menu in the <strong>Tickets</strong> tab, you can directly see in the ticket overview the tickets that have an attachment.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
